==Latin==
===Etymology===
The reference to [[Jesus Christ|Jesus]] is from the first three letters of Jesus' name in Greek, ΙΗΣΟΥΣ, arising perhaps circa 14th century.  The interpretation as an abbreviation [[Iesus]] [[hominium|Hominum]] [[salvator|Salvator]] is apparently a later back-formation when the Greek was no longer remembered.  (See [[w:Christogram|wikipedia Christogram]].)

==={{Initialism}}===
# In hoc signo (In this sign).  Commonly seen on Christian churches.
# [[Iesus]] [[hominium|Hominum]] [[salvator|Salvator]] (Jesus Savior of Men).

